name: Mackenzie Global Dividend ETF
longDescription: The fund investing primarily in equities of companies anywhere in the world that are expected to pay dividends. It may also invest in other types of securities that are expected to distribute income. The ETF will not invest more than 25% of its assets in emerging markets. The ETF seeks to provide longterm capital growth and current income.
